{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bf816c19-b9ee-4539-8bad-ac68ab19db79","content":"The issue is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files must be listed in dependency order. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` is listed first.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_vKJLzgXOcDAu5YfO0RY1e1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-d5312e33ced048e8944bfe4a5ce186d8/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-d5312e33ced048e8944bfe4a5ce186d8/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"3354efd8-d26e-4ef5-af0c-b5969dcce8a5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order in the `.fsproj` matters because F# uses a top-down compilation model — a file can only reference modules/types defined in files listed *above* it. \n\nIn the `.fsproj`, the order is:\n1. `Services.fs`\n2. `Domain.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`\n\nBut `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`). So `Domain.fs` must come before `Services.fs`. The correct order should be:\n1. `Domain.fs`\n2. `Services.fs`\n\n\n3. `Program.fs`","outputTokens":439,"requestId":"F03C:1EDE:225934:28C481:69F93E2B"},"id":"5e96b6ee-8e27-44f2-ba5b-fbc5ad5d5c02","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:47:47.434Z","parentId":"921f55ef-ff66-4d1e-a8e0-47cf51f18e8b"}
